"It's the 6th of May, 2019 as the email from the Amalthea arrives in my inbox, I was already declared as the core member and this new email tells me that the events coordinator is - you. The instant I had a look at the email, I knew that the events at Amalthea were going to be excellent when you were there to lead them, I never really got a chance to know you before that, but a preexistent respect, a pre existent belief in your sincerety, in your leadership and more importantly in your support already existed, and the next 3 years would prove all those initial thoughts to be true.

I have had most of my best memories at IITGN with you and I hope you can say the same. Indeed, be it the games we played, the walks we had, the spots we hung out at, the food we made, the movies we saw, the people we bitched about, the gossips we had, *pants* breathes in* *resumes rap again* the early morning breakfasts, the bike rides, the extra dishes ordered at restaurants, the tracking of orion at night and on and on. For other people reading this, I've just given you a list of things to do if you wanna have good time at IITGN, don't back away from sending me a thanks if you like it :)

Having you as a part of my life has been a blessing as you handle everything brilliantly. I have trusted you with my worst fears and my worst dejections and you have always been there to pat me on my back, give me some water, say some encouraging words and get me smiling and confident again (yupp, I might just be a dog). Thanks for being there to motivate me whenever I needed it. I am grateful to have you as a part of my life as I wouldn't have achieved all that I have if you weren't there. After all, who would have thought that a guy from state board would speak and write in such flawless english, a little help from an icse girl is all it takes :P
